div.div:
1. Bill and Jane registered blockchain-based identities once, before they ever met.
These identities are comprised of a user-selected, unique ID registered on the blockchain, whose ownership is provably tied to a set of pub/priv keys.

div.div: 2. Bill and Jane create a payload that includes their contract document, meta data (a time stamp, etc.), and signatures from their identity keys proving they agree to the document's state, when the agreement occurred, and all associated meta data.

div.div:
3. Bill and Jane save copies of the payload wherever they'd like in off-chain storage.
To prove the fact they both agreed to the contents of the payload, the state of the document when signed, and the time at which it was signed, Bill and Jane need only produce the payload and validate the identity signatures.
